title: [Wrought From Rot, Ledge]
description: Humidity soaks you in a bath of sticky air at the top of the hollowed out cypress.  Mold grows in dense clusters on the ceiling and wars silently with a moss-covered wall for territory in the corners.  The scent of mildew is protrusive.

Humidity saturates the air at the top of the hollowed out cypress and mold grows in dense clusters on the ceiling, warring silently with a moss-covered wall for territory in the corners.  The scent of mildew is protrusive.
